The paper discusses adversarial training and its impact on the tradeoff between robustness and accuracy in linear regression and neural networks. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
